the american french and indiana colors 
marching bands are a rarity in france and are considered 
quintessentially american but the most exotic spectacle came last 
with the 28 members of the touch of kyle twirling club of kalamazoo 
mich spinning their batons flags and pink rifles 
the events announcer addressing the crowd over speakers mounted 
at city hall described batontwirling as this very american art 
which consists of marching in time to the music spinning and 
tossing the little batons while executing all sorts of arabesques 
the young americans are participating in a variety of events 
marking the bicentennial around france 
i was really proud of our school that we got chosen said 
