a picture book of catherine the greats 
lewd furniture a cold war expose on communist sexual practices and 
pristine copies of playboy can be found among the 102 million tomes 
at harvard university 
but to see them you need to find the man who holds the key to 
the xr collection 
down a steep stairway at harvards widener library and behind a 
heavy copper door that stays locked is the collection that makes 
edward doctoroff the man with the key practically blush 
but if hes red in the face its not because of the erotic 
contents of the xr books and magazines but because the whole idea 
the locked collection is so oldfashioned and because the 
collection stopped growing years ago 
its a dead collection said the succinct doctoroff head of 
circulation services at widener the chief repository of the written 
word at harvard 
xr does not stand for xrated the x means the books 
are one of 20 categories of unusual books miniature books are 
another such category and the r stands for restricted 
marion schoon chief of the librarys reference collection 
believes as doctoroff does that its just an oddity of history that 
the assortment of 1000 books that analyze philosophize wax poetic 
about and poke fun at sex are still housed separately under lock 
and key 
this is sort of a remnant she said 
the xr collection was only actively assembled and added to for 
less than 30 years but the prudishness that was still the norm 
three decades ago had nothing to do with its separate status 
librarians were concerned about the books getting lost 
it was before my time but apparently in the 50s early 60s 
there was a sociology professor who found a lot of the books for his 
course were not available said ms schoon the books on the 
reading list that concerned sex were missing from wideners shelves 
so a restricted collection was created 
playboy had to be in there she added because they tended 
to lose the centerfold 
but librarians quit labeling books xr sometime in the 70s she 
said there was simply no need copies of the same books are now 
found in the general stacks but no one bothers to steal them or cut 
out their favorite pictures just over the road in harvard square 
newsstands sell plenty of magazines to satisfy the salacious scholar 
and playboy is on microfiche 
not much traffic goes on in the xr nowadays a week can go by 
with fewer than five volumes checked out 
so why continue to lock up sexual behavior in the communist 
