the books throughout harvards vast library and change all the 
records ms schoon said 
its sort of like a spiderweb cataloguing pulling all the 
cards its very labor intensive ms schoon said 
the library is plenty busy adding 50000 to 60000 new volumes 
every year reorganizing things for 1000 books could slow things 
down ms schoon said 
so the xr collection stays as it is a quaint memento of a time 
when sex needed to be kept under lock and key 
